    introContent: `
      <h2>Engineering Jobs in India – Complete Guide</h2>
      <p>Engineering is India's largest professional education stream, producing over 15 lakh graduates annually across branches including Computer Science, Mechanical, Civil, Electrical, Electronics, Chemical, and emerging fields like AI, Robotics, and Environmental Engineering. India's infrastructure boom (smart cities, highways, metro rail, renewable energy), manufacturing push (Make in India, PLI schemes), and technology sector growth create sustained demand for engineering talent. From design offices to construction sites, from R&D labs to production floors, engineers drive India's economic engine.</p>
      <p>The engineering job market in 2026 is being reshaped by several mega-trends. Electric vehicles (EVs) and renewable energy are creating new roles in automotive and power engineering. Industry 4.0 (IoT, AI, robotics, additive manufacturing) is transforming manufacturing. The semiconductor initiative is opening VLSI design and chip fabrication roles. Defence manufacturing under AtmaNirbhar Bharat is expanding opportunities for mechanical, aerospace, and electronics engineers. Smart city projects need civil, electrical, and urban planning engineers.</p>
      <h3>Engineering Branches & Opportunities</h3>
      <p>Computer Science & IT: highest hiring volume with software, AI, data, and cloud roles. Mechanical Engineering: automotive (Tata Motors, Maruti, Hyundai), manufacturing, HVAC, and defence. Civil Engineering: construction (L&T, Shapoorji Pallonji), real estate, government PWD, and infrastructure. Electrical Engineering: power companies (NTPC, PGCIL), renewable energy, and electrical equipment manufacturing. Electronics & Communication: telecom (Jio, Airtel), embedded systems, VLSI, and IoT. Chemical Engineering: petrochemicals, pharma, and FMCG manufacturing.</p>
      <h3>Salary Range</h3>
      <p>IT/CS freshers: ₹3-15 LPA (wide range based on company type). Core engineering freshers: ₹3-6 LPA. PSU engineers (through GATE): ₹8-14 LPA. Mechanical engineers at auto companies: ₹4-8 LPA. Civil engineers at L&T, Shapoorji: ₹4-8 LPA. R&D engineers: ₹6-15 LPA. Senior engineering managers: ₹15-35 LPA. Engineering consultants and CTOs: ₹30-80 LPA.</p>
      <h3>Key Certifications</h3>
      <p>GATE for PSU jobs and M.Tech admission. AutoCAD, SolidWorks, CATIA for mechanical/civil design. PMP for project management. AWS/Azure for IT infrastructure. Lean Six Sigma for manufacturing process improvement. LEED for green building professionals. Professional Engineer (PE) certification adds international credibility.</p>
      <h3>Career Advice for Engineering Graduates</h3>
      <p>Don't limit yourself to your branch—transferable skills (problem-solving, analytical thinking, project management) open doors across industries. Supplement technical knowledge with management skills for faster career growth. Core engineering PSU jobs offer stability and excellent benefits through GATE selection. Build practical experience through internships and industry projects during college. Register on TrueJobs to find engineering jobs matching your branch, experience level, and location preference.</p>
    `,
